l official acts binding the Hooker family to the colonial governor's wealth."},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"Yale man, militia captain, Assembly representative","body":"He graduated Yale College in 1729 and held the rank of Captain in the Connecticut Militia as early as 1734. He served as Hartford's representative in the General Assembly across three sessions, while running a substantial Hartford mercantile estate."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Son James partnered in Hooker & Chaffee","body":"His son James Hooker was a partner in the mercantile firm Hooker & Chaffee, which grew very successful during the Revolutionary War era. The firm continued the family's Hartford commercial standing into the next generation."}],"baptism":{"year":1710,"month":10,"day":8,"city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022","institution_blurb":"Yale College 1729.","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1729"}],"education":[{"school_name":"Yale College","graduation_year":1729,"institution_id":"INST022"}],"bio":{"display_name":"Captain Nathaniel Hooker","first_name":"Nathaniel","last_name":"Hooker","title":"Captain","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"nathaniel-hooker-1710"},"I00054":{"id":"I00054","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":true,"generation_from_john_talcott":3,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1709,"month":1,"day":26,"city":"Hartford","county":"Hartford County","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1795,"month":7,"day":12,"city":"Windsor","county":"Hartford County","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"T00045","mother_id":"U00017"},"marriages":[{